29/04/2007
OSLO, Norway -- Bucharest will host the next high-level summit of NATO in the spring of 2008, NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer said following the informal meeting of the Alliance's foreign ministers in Oslo on Friday (April 27th).
The same day, a meeting of the army chiefs-of-staff of the Adriatic Charter signatory states, as well as other Southeast European states that are part of NATO's Partnership for Peace programme, convened in Tirana on Friday. 
A joint declaration reaffirmed the common willingness for implementation of the criteria needed for full NATO integration. 
(Rompres, BNR, Pobjeda - 28/04/07; A1 TV, Albanian President website - 27/04/07)
